  "title": "Face to Face, Part II",
  "summary": "Continuing the tense evening at Bog's tavern on Tholatin, New Republic pilots Raxis, Rebecca, and Gene realize the Imperial Marshal Krieg and his agent Keline are present, and the cloak-and-dagger gives way to a direct, oddly civil confrontation. Krieg, using the alias 'Ian,' buys the rebels a round and trades pointed words about the necessity of order and the futility of endless war, with the hot-tempered Rebecca threatening to kill him and Raxis maintaining wary diplomacy; Krieg ultimately departs, preferring a known enemy and hinting at a coming duel. As Rebecca and Gene leave to find a hotel, two Imperial pilots, Wing Commander Dante and Liza Molokai, arrive and recognize Raxis as the ace 'Ghost 3.' The three pilots share drinks and spar verbally over the ethics of war, civilian deaths, and whether any ceasefire could ever end the bloodshed, Dante coolly insisting her job is simply to deal death. Liza plants a brief kiss on Raxis before excusing herself, and after more banter, Raxis pays Dante's tab and departs, the rivals parting on terms of grudging mutual respect.",
